:A high school graduate who joins the Eagle Jump games company as a character designer, as they made her favorite game. Due to her small stature, she is often mistaken for a middle school student.

;{{Nihongo|Ko Yagami|八神 コウ|Yagami Kō}}
:{{voiced by|[[Yōko Hikasa]]<ref name="ann-100333"/>|[[Michelle Rojas]]<ref name=":1" />}}
:The lead character designer of Eagle Jump. She spends a lot of time at the office, often sleeping there overnight in her underwear, and has a laid back but stern attitude. She was the character designer for the game that inspired Aoba to become one herself. After two years pass in the story, she goes to work at a games company in France alongside Wako's sister.

;{{Nihongo|Rin Tōyama|遠山 りん|Tōyama Rin}}
:{{voiced by|[[Ai Kayano]]<ref name="ann-100333"/>|Kristen McGuire<ref name=":1" />}}
:An art director and head of the background department. She is close friends with Ko and tends to get jealous when others get close to her. Unlike Ko, she is organized, well maintained and also a bit shy.

;{{Nihongo|Hifumi Takimoto|滝本 ひふみ|Takimoto Hifumi}}
:{{voiced by|Megumi Yamaguchi<ref name="ann-100333"/>|Jill Harris<ref name=":1" />}}
:A character designer. She is shy talking to others and prefers to speak via e-mail. She has a pet hedgehog named Sōjirō and secretly enjoys [[cosplay]].

;{{Nihongo|Yun Iijima|飯島 ゆん|Iijima Yun}}
:{{voiced by|Ayumi Takeo<ref name="ann-100333"/>|[[Leah Clark]]<ref name=":1" />}}
:A character designer who designs monsters and often dresses in gothic clothing. She has two younger siblings.

;{{Nihongo|Hajime Shinoda|篠田 はじめ|Shinoda Hajime}}
:{{voiced by|[[Megumi Toda]]<ref name="ann-100333"/>|[[Tia Ballard]]<ref name=":1" />}}
:A motion designer who works in the character design department as there are no open seats in the animation department. She later takes on the additional role of game planner. She enjoys [[sentai]] shows and owns various prop weapons.

;{{Nihongo|Umiko Ahagon|阿波根 うみこ|Ahagon Umiko}}
:{{voiced by|[[Chitose Morinaga]]<ref name="ng-anime-spotlight">{{cite web|title=Anime Spotlight - New Game!|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/anime-spotlight/2016/summer/new-game/.103847|publisher=[[Anime News Network]]|accessdate=December 10, 2016|date=July 11, 2016}}</ref>|[[Caitlin Glass]]<ref name=":1" />}}
:A programmer who often gets annoyed when she has to fix errors and is embarrassed by her surname. She is a military fan and has several airsoft weapons in her workspace.

;{{nihongo|Nene Sakura|桜 ねね|Sakura Nene}}
:{{voiced by|Madoka Asahina<ref name="ng-anime-spotlight"/>|[[Bryn Apprill]]<ref name=":1" />}}
:Aoba's friend from high school who is currently in university. After working a summer job as a debugger for Eagle Jump, she takes an interest in designing games herself and soon joins the company as a programmer in Umiko's department.

;{{Nihongo|Shizuku Hazuki|葉月 しずく|Hazuki Shizuku}}
:{{voiced by|[[Eri Kitamura]]<ref name="ng-anime-spotlight"/>|[[Carli Mosier]]<ref name=":1" />}}
:A game director with a strong interest in cute girls, hence why her department is entirely female. She is often told off by Umiko for sneaking from her workstation and making impulsive changes to the game design. She owns a cat named Mozuku.

;{{nihongo|Wako Christina Yamato|大和・クリスティーナ・和子|Yamato Kurisutīna Wako}}
:{{voiced by|[[Kaori Nazuka]]<ref name="ng-season2-cast">{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2017-05-22/new-game-anime-season-2-reveals-4-new-cast-members/.116390|title=New Game!! Anime Season 2 Reveals 4 New Cast Members|website=Anime News Network|date=May 22, 2017|accessdate=May 22, 2017}}</ref>|Elizabeth Maxwell<ref name="VA">{{cite web|url=https://www.funimation.com/blog/2017/07/13/summer-2017-simuldubs-funimationnow/|title=Summer 2017 SimulDubs on FunimationNow!|website=Funimation|date=August 19, 2017}}</ref>}}
:A half-French producer who works at Eagle Jump's publishing company, Houbundo. Although often having a strict appearance, she is shy around others. Her sister works at a games company in France.

;{{nihongo|Momiji Mochizuki|望月 紅葉|Mochizuki Momiji}}
:{{voiced by|Arisa Suzuki<ref name="ng-season2-cast"/>|[[Jad Saxton]]}}
:A girl who joins Eagle Jump as a graphic artist during the story's second year. She lives with Tsubame, who calls her "Momo" for short, and considers Aoba to be her rival.

;{{nihongo|Tsubame Narumi|鳴海 ツバメ|Narumi Tsubame}}
:{{voiced by|[[Hitomi Ohwada]]<ref name="ng-season2-cast"/>|Jeannie Tirado}}
:A girl who joins Eagle Jump as a programmer during the story's second year, nicknamed "Naru". 

;{{nihongo|Hotaru Hoshikawa|星川 ほたる|Hoshikawa Hotaru}}
:{{voiced by|[[Manaka Iwami]]<ref name="ng-season2-cast"/>|Madeleine Morris}}
:Aoba and Nene's friend from high school, who was part of their school's Art Club. She is a skilled artist but has a weak condition. She is currently studying at a fine arts college in order to become a professional illustrator.

;{{nihongo|Chinatsu Hidaka|日高 ちなつ|Hidaka Chinatsu}}
:A teacher in Aoba and Nene's high school, who is good friends with Hotaru. Despite being an advisor for the Art Club, she has no drawing skills of her own and often prefers to play baseball.

==Media==
===Manga===
The original manga by Shōtarō Tokunō began serialization in [[Houbunsha]]'s ''[[Manga Time Kirara Carat]]'' magazine from January 28, 2013. Houbunsha has published seven ''[[tankōbon]]'' volumes between February 27, 2014 and March 27, 2018.<ref name="houbunsha">{{cite web|url=http://houbunsha.co.jp/comics/detail.php?p=%A3%CE%A3%C5%A3%D7%A1%A1%A3%C7%A3%C1%A3%CD%A3%C5%A1%AA|title=New Game!|publisher=[[Houbunsha]]|accessdate=July 27, 2016|language=Japanese}}</ref> The fifth volume, subtitled ''The Spinoff!'', takes place prior to the main series and features content not included in the magazine serialization.<ref name="houbunsha"/> [[Seven Seas Entertainment]] licensed the series in North America.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2017-07-03/seven-seas-licenses-made-in-abyss-nameless-asterism-soul-liquid-chambers-getter-robo-devolution-manga/.118351|title=Seven Seas Licenses Made in Abyss, Nameless Asterism, Soul Liquid Chambers, Getter Robo Devolution Manga|publisher=[[Anime News Network]]|date=July 3, 2017|accessdate=July 3, 2017}}</ref>

