===Anime===
{{see also|List of New Game! episodes}}
A 12-episode anime television series adaptation aired in Japan between July 4 and September 19, 2016 and was simulcast by [[Crunchyroll]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2016-07-01/crunchyroll-adds-b-project-new-game-bananya-hitori-no-shita-the-outcast/.103875|title=Crunchyroll Adds B-Project, New Game!, Bananya, Hitori no Shita the outcast|publisher=[[Anime News Network]]|date=July 1, 2016|accessdate=July 10, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://newgame-anime.com/product/|title=Product｜TVアニメ『New Game!』オフィシャルサイト|publisher=[[Doga Kobo]]|accessdate=July 10, 2016|language=Japanese}}</ref> The anime is produced by [[Doga Kobo]], with Yoshiyuki Fujiwara as the director and [[Fumihiko Shimo]] as the series' script supervisor, featuring character designs by Ai Kikuchi.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/daily-briefs/2016-01-23/engaged-to-the-unidentified-team-animates-new-game-show-at-doga-kobo/.97896|title='Engaged to the Unidentified' Team Animates 'New Game' Show at Doga Kobo|publisher=Anime News Network|date=January 23, 2016|accessdate=January 23, 2016}}</ref> An [[original video animation]] (OVA) episode was made available for those who purchased all six Blu-ray/DVD volumes of the series, released between September 28, 2016 and February 24, 2017.<ref name="OVA">{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2016-09-14/new-game-tv-anime-blu-rays-dvds-to-offer-public-bath-ova/.106448|title=New Game! TV Anime's Blu-rays/DVDs to Offer Public Bath OVA|publisher=[[Anime News Network]]|date=September 14, 2016|accessdate=September 14, 2016}}</ref> The opening and ending themes respectively are {{nihongo|"Sakura Skip"|SAKURAスキップ|Sakura Sukippu}} and "Now Loading!!!", both performed by Fourfolium ([[Yūki Takada]], Megumi Yamaguchi, Ayumi Takeo, and [[Megumi Toda]]). A second season titled ''New Game!!'' aired in Japan between July 11 and September 26, 2017 and was simulcast by Crunchyroll.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2017-07-11/crunchyroll-to-stream-new-game-season-2-in-another-world-with-my-smartphone-anime/.118658|title=Crunchyroll to Stream New Game!! Season 2, In Another World With My Smartphone Anime|publisher=[[Anime News Network]]|date=July 11, 2017|accessdate=July 11, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/daily-briefs/2017-06-02/new-game-anime-premieres-on-july-11/.116930|title=New Game!! Anime Premieres on July 11|website=Anime News Network|date=June 2, 2017|accessdate=June 2, 2017}}</ref> The second season's opening theme is "Step by Step Up ↑↑↑↑" while the ending themes are "Jumpin' Jump Up!!!!" for the first six episodes and {{nihongo|"Yumeiro Compass"|ユメイロコンパス|Dream-colored Compass}} for episode seven onwards, all performed by Fourfolium.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2017-05-10/new-game-anime-season-2-reveals-anime-theme-song-artist/.115899|title=New Game! Anime Season 2 Reveals Anime's Theme Song Artist|website=Anime News Network|date=May 10, 2017|accessdate=June 2, 2017}}</ref> The series is licensed in North America by [[Crunchyroll]], and [[Funimation]] dubbed and released it on home video.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.crunchyroll.com/anime-news/2018/06/18/crunchyroll-and-funimation-reveal-new-slate-of-home-video-releases |title=Crunchyroll and Funimation Reveal New Slate of Home Video Releases |date=June 18, 2018 |website=[[Crunchyroll]] |accessdate=June 19, 2018 }}</ref>

===Video games===
A [[visual novel]] developed by [[5pb.]], titled ''New Game!: The Challenge Stage'', was released for [[PlayStation 4]] and [[PlayStation Vita]] in Japan on January 26, 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.siliconera.com/2016/07/20/first-screens-new-game-challenge-stage-show-aoba-hifumi-kou-shizuku/|title=First Screens Of New Game! The Challenge Stage! Show Aoba, Hifumi, Kou, And Shizuku|publisher=Siliconera|date=July 20, 2016|accessdate=July 20, 2016}}</ref> Characters from the series also appear alongside other ''Manga Time Kirara'' characters in the 2017 mobile [[Role-playing video game|role-playing game]] ''[[Kirara Fantasia]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2017-06-25/houbunsha-reveals-kirara-fantasy-smartphone-rpg/.117972|title=Houbunsha Reveals Kirara Fantasy Smartphone RPG|publisher=[[Anime News Network]]|date=June 25, 2017|accessdate=June 29, 2017}}</ref>

