{{About|the French organisation|the [[cell adhesion molecule]]|L-selectin|the proposed Horry County, South Carolina road|Southern Evacuation Lifeline}} {{refimprove|date=October 2013}}
{{Infobox organization |name = Syndicat des éditeurs de logiciels de loisirs |image = |image_border = |size = |alt = |caption = |map = |msize = |malt = |mcaption = |abbreviation = SELL |motto = |formation = 1995 |extinction = |type = |status = |purpose = Promote the interests of video game developers |headquarters = |location = |region_served = France |membership = |language = |leader_title = |leader_name = |main_organ = |parent_organization = |affiliations = |num_staff = |num_volunteers = |budget = |website = |remarks = }}
'''SELL''' ('''Syndicat des éditeurs de logiciels de loisirs''') is a French organisation that promotes the interests of video game developers. The group mainly distributes information about video game professionals to authorities and consumers. Created in 1995, the group is chaired by [[Philippe Sauze]] from [[Electronic Arts]] France. The general delegate is [[Jean Claude Larue]] (ex. [[Infogrames Entertainment, SA|Infogrames]]).
From June 1999 until the arrival in 2003 of [[Pan European Game Information|PEGI]], the organisation rated the content of video games in France. Their classification system had four categories: "tous publics" (all audiences), "12 ans et plus" (12 years and over), "16 ans et plus" (16 years and over), and "interdit aux moins de 18 ans" (restricted under 18 years).
