{{Infobox artwork | image_file = Goya - Die Weinlese - 1786.jpeg | image_size = 250px | title = The Grape Harvest or Autumn | other_language_1 = Spanish | other_title_1 = La vendimia o El Otoño | artist = [[Francisco Goya]] | year = 1786 | medium = [[Oil painting|Oil]] on [[canvas]] | height_metric = 267.5 | width_metric = 190.5 | city = [[Madrid]] | museum = [[Museo del Prado]] }}
'''''The Grape Harvest or Autumn''''' ({{lang-es|La vendimia o El Otoño}}) is a 1786 oil on canvas painting by [[Francisco&nbsp;Goya]] which depicts a man in autumn-colored clothes with his wife and son. A peasant is presenting them with a sample of the year’s grape harvest.<ref name="Prado">{{cite web |title=The Grape Harvest or Autumn |work=Museo del Prado |url=https://www.museodelprado.es/en/the-collection/online-gallery/on-line-gallery/obra/the-grape-harvest-or-autumn/ |dead-url=no |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151104202200/http://www.museodelprado.es/en/the-collection/online-gallery/on-line-gallery/obra/the-grape-harvest-or-autumn/ |archive-date=2015-11-04 |df= }}</ref> The piece has been held by the [[Museo del Prado]] in [[Madrid]] since 1870.<ref name="Prado"/>
